ssociates november    am eastern daylight time miami  londonbusiness wirethe hackett group inc nasdaqhckt and the chartered institute of management accountants cima today announced the launch of their diploma in global business services dgbs this is the third and final offering in their certified gbs professionals cgbsp program a comprehensive career development system for global business services gbs shared services and business process outsourcing bpo professionals the diploma in gbs designed for current gbs team leaders center managers and others running operational or functional teams covers an array of topics relevant to operational excellence in finance hr procurement and it it is the middle level of certification offered by the cgbsp program the program also offers an advanced diploma for leaders and members of a gbs organization’s senior management team as well as a certificate in gbs designed for entrylevel associates more than  organizations from over  countries are already engaged in offering certification to their gbs shared services or bpo staff through the cgbsp program each level of certification is driven by a comprehensive syllabus that teaches the skills and competencies required by employers to achieve the highest standards of excellence at the foundation of the course materials are the hackett group’s extensive knowledge of gbs and functional best practices based on its strategy design and implementation work with top global enterprises combined with cima’s intellectual content and longterm education expertise the certification programs are selfpaced online interactive learning tools that employees can complete over three to four months computerbased objective test exams are available in over  centers worldwide and are professionally supervised to ensure the robustness of the assessment participants in these programs also have access to an online knowledge center offering access to materials such as case studies frameworks and performance metrics from the hackett group cima and other organizations the knowledge center is designed to support participants through exams and lifelong learning with additional material unlocked as individuals complete certification at each level on successful completion of each course assessment individuals earn the right to use the relevant professional qualification designation of cgbs dgbs or adgbs to coincide with the launch of the dgbs qualification the cgbsp program is making available for download on a complimentary basis its first gbs research piece “building new career paths the emergence of the global business services professional” at httpbitlydnfp a selfassessment tool available at httpbitlyxkimk is also available to help organizations and professionals determine which of the certification programs is best suited to their needs “it’s exciting to be able to announce the availability of the final element of this comprehensive training and certification program” said ted a fernandez chairman  ceo of the hackett group “as companies become more mature and sophisticated in their gbs operations it’s critical that they improve the agility and flexibility of their workforce to better meet the changing needs and expectations of the business the success of a gbs organization is highly dependent on the knowledge and capabilities of staff and the training and certification we’re offering can play an important role in helping companies accomplish this” “we are proud to bring to market a unique offering that combines cima’s training expertise with the empiricallyproven best practices and intellectual property only the hackett group can provide” said mr fernandez “the combination of training testing accreditation and a knowledge centre to help staff keep up with new developments and trends is unique and fills an unmet need across the gbs organizations we work with” andrew harding fcma cgma chief executive of cima said “we believe this is a major step forward for the gbs industry now that this final part of the offering is in place gbs professionals have industrystandard qualifications available to them no matter where they are in their careers we believe this will help the gbs and shared services sector allowing organisations to provide their staff with the necessary skills to reach their full potential “we are living in a fast paced world and people need the right competencies to adapt to new challenges our program uses the latest technology and we are able to provide the opportunity for longterm success” the hackett group’s research clearly quantifies the bottomline benefit of gbs excellence worldclass gbs organizations generate far greater initial savings over baseline costs than typical gbs organizations  percent savings versus  percent they also drive  percent higher savings on an annual ongoing basis finally better talent management drives an array of bottomline benefits including nearly  percent higher return on equity and higher net profit margins and ebitda training plays a key role in achieving these results with worldclass gbs organizations offering managers and staff nearly three times the training hours of typical organizations the research also shows that the gbs evolution is accelerating the hackett group estimates that there are now over  gbs centers globally with a total staff of more than  million the majority of gbs organizations have moved beyond singlefunction centers to establish multifunction centres but less than  percent of all gbs organizations have completed the evolution to create fully integrated services environments with an endtoend process orientation and a comprehensive service catalogue for more information on the certified global business services professionals program and its advanced diploma in gbs please visit httpwwwthehackettgroupcomexpertisegbstraining about the certified global business services professionals program the certified global business services professionals program is a collaboration between